social_posts.post_text:
What. Just. Happened. Art After Dark kicked off Wednesday night with our VIP Opening Dinner & Cocktail Party and boy, it did not disappoint! What started as an idea only a few months ago, truly came together in an unfathomable amount of time and I am so humbled and grateful to the many people who made it all possible. My one and only sister @suehyunr and @jiparknyc of @artlineny, thank you for being the best partners throughout all of this and for bringing this concept to life. To our brilliantly talented and generous friends/collectors who lent their world class art - I hope we have made you proud! @Americanexpress, @resy, @aaron_ginsberg it’s quite simple: this event would not have happened without your dedication and tremendous partnership. Thank you for joining us on this ride from day one. To our incredible partners and vendors @rockawaymore, @worldredeye, Bggy Studio, @tentoonerum, @chopinvodka & @casadragones, you are incredible and your talents were brought to the forefront last night. Saving the best for last: TEAM COTE! What would I do without you dragon slayers? I am only as good as my colleagues and I feel so blessed and humbled to work with some of the best in this industry. Huge shout out to the entire team for going on this wild journey with me and executing everything so flawlessly. You make me proud day in and day out. If you haven’t booked your reservation yet, Art After Dark will be available for the public to enjoy through December 9. Hope to see you @cotemiami soon!
Forgot to mention very special thanks to @_kbanx @jacqhensel @eastandbulltomiami @nataliebud - MVP. Love you guys!

Art Basel may have ended, but the party continues: COTE’s Art After Dark menu and one-of-a-kind art pieces are on display through this Friday, December 9. Consider this your final warning for 🥩+🔥+🍸= 😊 

Head to @cotemiami to reserve your dine!
Thank you so much @Forbes for recognizing @cotenyc in your 2022 All-Star Eateries in New York! Congratulations to the hardest working team in the game for making this all possible 🙏🏻 🐉

My Team. My Fam. My heart is full! What a pleasure to celebrate the holidays with the entire crew of dragon slayers. Words cannot express how grateful I am to have these badasses on my team. I wish all of you happy and healthy holidays and look forward to crushing life and kicking ass again and again and again and again. I love you dragon slayers! ❤️

Quick PSA: It’s back! Time to show up to your holiday gathering with a dish that will undoubtedly make you rockstar for the day: our fall-off-the-bone Galbi Jjim. It's an epic feast with our USDA Prime short rib seasoned with sweet soy sauce, shiitake mushrooms, daikon, carrots, ginkgo nuts, and chestnuts. We cook overnight until its fall-off-the-bone tender.

We're including four packs of Korean white rice with every order, which you can easily heat up via your microwave in just three minutes.

Pre-orders can be placed now until Wednesday, December 21, 2022 by 6pm EST.

Available for pick-up at COTE NYC on December 23 or December 24!

Visit cotenyc.com or hit the link in bio to pre-order!

⚡️⚡️⚡️Something Legendary has landed @cote_nyc!  @chefdavidshim, @chefskkim and the entire culinary team have been innovating and refining on the procurement and execution of a new dish for the last 9 months. IT’S FINALLY. HERE. Want to see the most badass dish COTE has prepared to-date? STARTS TOMORROW! THIS IS GOING TO BE BIG! ⚡️⚡️⚡️

Merry Christmas from me & my sweet mama.
I hope your holidays are filled with great wine and food. Good friends and family. Loud giggles and laughters. Good health and big joy! I am grateful for all the love and support I received this year. Can’t wait to welcome the new year and look forward to another year of hard work and gratefulness. 

Mi Amor Mom!

Happy New Year! I wish all of you very happy and healthy new year. 🙏🏽❤️👍🏽
What a year it was. This past year really has been packed with so much. So much joy but there were moments of deep sadness and sorrow. But all in all, I am beyond grateful for all the blessings, fond memories and great learnings that took place this year. I am also grateful for the events that were sad, scary, and difficult, as they gave me the opportunity a to grow and mature. Year 2022 truly was a year that I will remember forever. I love you, Life. Thank you, God. 
.
.
.
Year 2023, HERE. WE. COME!!
Dragon Slayers, you ready????

Happy New Year.
Let’s wrap ourselves in sense of gratitude and determination and crush year 2023! Let’s go!

Last evening, @stevecuozzo & the @nypost announced the news that we will be partnering with The Olayan Group to bring a new, multi-faceted dining concept to @550madison (link in bio). This venture marks a momentous phase for Gracious Hospitality Management and I am immensely proud and grateful to be working on such an exciting project for New York City. The creative process is something that I deeply love and that truly excites me especially when I have the opportunity to collaborate with some of the most talented and excellence-driven professionals in the world. While I really can't share any additional details right now, I am looking forward to "the big reveal" down the road.

Last week, the @cote_nyc team spent the afternoon volunteering at @cityharvestnyc's new Food Rescue Center in Sunset Park, Brooklyn. We receive so much love from our community, so it’s incredibly meaningful when we have the opportunity to spread the love back. What a privilege to support one of the most impactful nonprofits in the country and serve our NYC neighbors in need - all while having an absolute freaking blast with the dragon slayers! Working together as a team, we repacked over 18,000 pounds of apples to be distributed to community food partners all across the five boroughs. Epic day and looking forward to many more to come! #wearecityharvest

Tom, aka @tbinno , thank you for EVERYTHING! We love you to the moon and back ! Thank you for your dedication, heart of 24k gold, and the most wholesome nurture. We will not be who we are without your steadfast TLC and guidance. We are forever grateful. Your uniquely nurturing and genuine qualities will forever live in GHM through all of us. We salute you!❤️

Thank you so much @michelinguide for featuring our new Legend of the Seven Jades as your Dish of the Moment (link in bio). Such a joy to speak to the ethos behind this dish that took @chefdavidshim, @chefskkim and our culinary team over nine months to develop. Hope you’ll stop in to @cotenyc soon to try it out for yourself!  @garyhe thank you for the epic shot 📸🫶🏽
Magique daddy-daughter lunch at this magical 7 star ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️restaurant. #grateful  merci (and bravo !) Chef @ericripert for the most over the top generosity….🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽❤️

Commissioned by the one and only @paulaperlis (thank you!❤️) , we delivered a very special family meal to @lebernardinny to congratulate them on their ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ victory! Hope everyone at the Cathedral of fine seafood enjoyed a Korean Steakhouse family meal!  @cote_nyc and @cotemiami wish you many, many more years of blessing and victories! Bravo to the entire team LB and Chef @ericripert ! 👍🏽❤️🙏🏽 #grateful
Love it when the universe just brings it all together ❤️! #grateful #bigboss missed you @chefskkim

Double Shark Attack!
Two Sharks 🦈 showed up separately, met up at @cotemiami ! They must have smelled the 🩸 🥩! Always great to welcome you @thesharkdaymond @kevinolearytv !
Happy born day @foodgod !
Lots of love, @wyclefjean . Best of wishes with all the amazing projects ahead! 🙏🏽🙏🏽👍🏽 🏎️❤️

As we close out two amazing years @cotemiami, it has been hard to put into words the appreciation I have for this beautiful, vibrant city. Seeing myself staring back at me in the March issue of @aventuramagazine is this crazy introspective that’s been captured on paper by the talented @slissmia and @tolgakavut.
 
I know what attracted me to this city and I know what I wanted COTE to be when we embarked on this journey. Miami, you have done so right by me.
 
They say timing is everything and so I’m soaking up this moment and feeling very loved and very grateful.

For the first time after 30 dynamic years, @nas finally graced @thegarden with his presence ! I grew up listening to Nas and Hate Me Now was one of my favorite songs. The song hit me quite different last night - hearing it in sold-out, one-night only concert at the one and only Madison Square Garden. So much has changed since I first fell in love with the song as a teenager. But one thing remains as the constant : Nas is the 🐐 of hip hop. So grateful that I was able to be part of this historical performance!

Incredible evening with @apexforyouth last night, including a tour of @wangechimutu’s exhibition led by Apex board member and former Deputy Director of the @newmuseum, Karen Wong. Most inspiring was hearing from Apex student Ruhshona, who shared her personal story and just how impactful Apex has been on her journey. Proud and honored to support such an important and impactful organization. Can’t wait for their Gala on Wednesday, April 26th! Giant thanks to the entire team at Apex for their unstoppable efforts in uplifting our children! ❤️🙏🏽🫰🏽

HERE.WE.GO!
Four plus years in the making and I am beyond excited to reveal what is next for Gracious Hospitality Management. We have worked tirelessly on R&D and after many failures and struggles, and some more failures and struggles and deep frustration, it finally happened.

That huge breakthrough moment when the stars align and it all makes perfect sense. 

I can’t wait to share our new fried chicken concept with you. It’s unlike any other you’ve seen. This is for everyone. More news coming soon! Special thanks to @chefskkim @dexterlovelacezimet @pentagramdesign @rockwellgroup and countless others that put so much in to this project! You know who you are.

More news coming soon!

I am beyond grateful to be receiving this great plaque of honor on behalf of the entire team at @cote_nyc from the one and only @michelinguide . I am extremely proud of @chefdavidshim and the entire team Cote for their commitment to excellence, day in and day out. I always viewed this great honor not as a “job well done” for what we did yesterday, but as “cheers” to doing a better job tomorrow. Thank you @michelinguide for allowing all us to feel recognized and appreciated for what we do every single day. Thank you, our financial and professional partners for your trust, support, and collaboration. Thank you, our loyal customers! Thank you, Dragon Slayers! So much love ❤️ and gratefulness! Special thanks to the one and only @garyhe for the very special photos 🫶🏽 missing you @w.sohn @theofficialdeeganmcclung

I have learned much over the years but if there's one big lesson to be shared it's this: Happiness truly stems not from what we get but what we give. The power of giving, the power of community, the power of helping those who need it most. It's at the fabric of everything - how I run my business, how my team succeeds, how I hope to parent.

I came to America from Seoul when I was thirteen years old and I learned very quickly that it's not easy being the immigrant kid who looks different. Not in the least. But I made it through. I leaned on mentors and members of my community. I knew that the only way ahead was through. 

Now, through my work with @apexforyouth, what a privilege to come full circle and help the next rising generation of AAPI superstars. Together, We Are Unstoppable because there is no other way.

I'm so humbled and deeply moved to be one of their honorees at this year's 31st Inspiration Awards Gala taking place on Wednesday, April 26. If you can, I hope you'll join us to help pave the way and empower future thousands of under-resourced Asian and Immigrant youth. Because if we don't, who will?

Please follow the link in bio for ways to support the gala!❤️🫶🏽
Always appreciate a lady that appreciates oysters 🦪. (…and 🍋 lemonade)  #merci @chefjgv @tinbuilding

October 2015.
Piora. 피어라
My first restaurant. 
@victoria___james and I had just started working together. She began as our first Wine Director. And while we didn’t really know what we were doing, we wholeheartedly trusted each other to find our paths. And your path became redefining what the world of beverage could be.

One thing led to another and hot damn. You built the most outstanding beverage program one could ask for. You empowered female, BIPOC-led small producers while simultaneously creating the most talented team who are motivated daily with you at the helm. You founded @wineempowered with the equally powerful @amyeatsrice. You helped us thrive through a pandemic and remain the most dedicated Director of Beverage. Most notably, you are also an incredible mother. I’m so proud to have watched you thrive in all your roles but especially as a Mom to Simone.
Victoria, I’m so honored to have worked alongside you all these years. 

And then came @miavandewater. Those who know her are aware of her picture perfect professional pedigree. But she is so much more than her resume. She is an encyclopedia of knowledge. She is meticulous. She is as soft as if she fierce. With Mia on board, our beverage program has soared to new heights and beyond. And now, as our new Director of Education, she will pave the way via COTE College for any employee under our roof to receive wine education, free of charge!!!!, empowering our people while continuing to refine the craft and elevate our game. 

Lastly, our unbelievable Sommelier team of badasses, our Norwegian cocktail slayer leading the forces at @undercote @mrkasin and the entire beverage team. You are the dragon slayers who help keep the beating heart of COTE alive. 

Thank you so much to all of our COTE friends and family for six years of unwavering love.

It is with sincere pride and gratitude to be named as a finalist in the 2023 Outstanding Wine and Beverage program category at the @beardfoundation awards @cote_nyc ! Our third year to receive this immense honor. Thank you @beardfoundation and see you in Chicago!!!

A secret agent car for a secret asian man 🙌🏾 Grateful to @thecollectionfl for an amazing experience with the @astonmartin DBX 707. This was one of the most fun and exhilarating driving experiences. 

From smooth riding on GT mode, to absolute beast mode unleashing all 707 hp at Sports + mode, it was just so much fun to spend a week with this beast. Throw in posh details in finishes and killer sounds system, this sexy British beast was also beyond classy! Dragon Slayers loved being taken out for a joy ride! 🙏🏽❤️

A big thank you to @thecollectionfl for the generosity, expertise and highest quality of service, the best team in town for your next ride ❤️🙏🏽👍🏽
Three Kings and I.

Incredible time had at this year’s @miamiopen! Thank you for hosting us, Chez Simone.

We teamed up with our friends from @lacoste to offer a one-day luxury culinary experience during the Men’s Singles and Women’s Doubles Finals at the 2023 Miami Open. Guests were treated to USDA prime cuts of meat via a live plancha experience with @chefdavidshim, our kick-ass “Shicken” sandwich and fried chicken. It wouldn’t be a COTE event without our signature @petrossiannyc caviar bumps because... #caviarmadeusdoit

Take a look back at some of the highlights from this action-packed day with some of our dragon slayers in the Magic City. Thank you for having us Team Lacoste – @jasekim & @deyvanshi!

#cotemiami #lacoste #miamiopen #hardrockstadium #caviarinmiami

What could be better than learning from the best talent in the biz and therefore getting closer to your career goals? Doing it, free of charge, while on payroll. Thanks to @miavandewater, @victoria___james and all the 🍷 dragon slayers for putting together this amazing program for our staff. COTE College is a 12-week intensive wine program that’s available to all staff at all COTE locations and it doesn’t cost a dime. I am deeply grateful and delighted for what this will mean for current and future staff and I’m proud to continue supporting this rockstar team!❤️

"One of the greatest lessons I have learned throughout my career is to be yourself. When you're in fine dining, the business can be very theatrical. You're always playing a role - it can be exhausting. If you can find yourself and be yourself in that role then you're no longer playing it. Your words and actions become much more authentic and profound." - @SimonKimNYC, Founder & President of Gracious Hospitality Management and Proprietor of Cote Korean Steakhouse (@cote_nyc & @cotemiami)

#GetInspired by Simon's career path and and advice that he has learned along the way on #CulinaryAgents.com #HospitalityCareerPaths #NotJustJobs #ConnectingTheIndustry
With my favorite people at my dad’s favorite restaurant. Thanks for the cutest welcome, and the baddest dinner, Chef @richtorrisi !🫡👍🏽❤️

I immigrated to America when I was 13 years old and as I shared in front of a packed room at @apexforyouth’s Annual Gala this past Wednesday evening, it wasn’t an easy transition. I was a mentee who needed a mentor. 

Fast forward to now, and what a moment it was to stand in this room and receive Apex’s 31st Inspiration Award with so many of my mentors sitting right there in front of me, most especially my Dad. @edwkim, @suehyunr, Paul Choi, Michael Chung @ecbigdaddy  @jrdhecla and many more: you are the one’s who helped get me to that stage. I will be forever grateful to you.

I have received many accolades over my career but none as meaningful and as motivating as this. Jiyoon Chung, your incredible stewardship of one of the most important organizations in the AAPI community has touched the lives of so many in our community. Huge congratulations to you and the entire Apex team for raising over $3.2 million(!!!) to empower Asian American and immigrant youth. 

Aria Hussain, you did an outstanding job sharing your story as an Apex mentee and brilliant aspiring medical professional. I see a dragon slayer in you!

@misschloeflower, you took the house down with your killer performance. Thank you for honoring me with your heartfelt introduction - you’re the best! 

To my family: My Mom, Dad, Sister, Nayun, Dani, and Eunu you are my world and motivate me to keep fighting for good.

Wen Zhou and @therealphilliplim for your tremendous leadership in the AAPI community and beyond - and for your unwavering friendship and support. 

Last but NEVER least, my epic team of Dragon Slayers at Gracious Hospitality Management: Having many of you there that evening was something I’ll never forget. It’s an honor to serve with you today and always. Thanks for standing with me through thick and thin.

Thanks to all my friends, partners, and God for these blessings. I’m very grateful for this beautiful life and for the opportunity to serve. Together, we are truly UNSTOPPABLE!

Lastly, I dedicate this honor to the person who positively impacted me more than anyone else combined: Captain.

@cityharvestnyc’s epic 40th Anniversary Gala was nothing short of magical.

I’ve been a Board and Food Council member for a number of years and City Harvest’s mission of feeding New York families in need is deeply important to me. In honor of their 40th Anniversary and our shared 1982 birth year, I knew we had to bring out all the other big guns born in 1982. I called my incredible friends and culinary superstars @roni_mazumdar, @stefanosecchi, Nozomu Abe (@sushinoz), @chefchintan and of course, @chefdavidshim, for a once-in-a-lifetime summer dinner party.

I am so humbled and grateful to share that our live auction lot went for $220k not once, but twice! $440,000 is enough to feed more than 1 million to New Yorkers in need. It’s hard to wrap that around my head but I am just so proud to be able to do what we can to share the love back with our city.

Thank you so much @jillystephens, @gregorycharvest, @kathyholding and the entire City Harvest team. Huge congratulations to the Board, Food Council, and loyal donors for raising over $5M. Such a magical evening!

 #WeAreCityHarvest
Congratulations to this hard working, dedicated team @cotemiami !🙏🏽 thank you @michelinguide 🙇🏻‍♂️

“COTE is a Korean Steakhouse, not Korean BBQ, but it features many of the same qualities, including energy and conviviality,” says Simon Kim the mastermind behind @cote_nyc and @cotemiami. In honor of Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month, @judyjoochef gets up close and personal with her Seoul brother @simonkimnyc for @UsWeekly. Simon reveals his extraordinary journey both inside and outside the restaurant, including his deep-rooted passion for dining (nurtured by his Korean upbringing), the secret behind COTE’s remarkable success and his extensive philanthropic endeavors.
 
Plus, try Simon’s coveted Dolsot Bibimbap recipe at home! Head over to the link in bio to read the entire Q&A and recipe.
GRATEFUL.

Thank you @shakeshack team, @dhmeyer & @randygarutti for inviting me as this month's speaker for AAPI History Month at your corporate office! Grateful to have the opportunity to share my story, talk about @apexforyouth, and meet so many talented people over some epic bites. I've always been a huge fan of the brand and truly got to see firsthand how incredibly talented the people are that make it so successful. We ❤️ you Shake Shack!

A day of tennis + gorgeous weather + industry legends + amazing lineup of chefs and restaurants - all for an imperative cause to help feed hungry New Yorkers = what could be better? Congratulations @karlitz_co for producing another outstanding year hosting the Celebrity Chefs & Friends Golf and Tennis Tournament benefitting @cityharvestnyc. Together, we raised enough to help feed 944,000 New Yorkers in need for a day! Bravo to hot shot Golf Chair @geoffreyzakarian and my favorite Tennis Co-chair @kheffernan212 for your leadership. Huge congrats to @chefalfredportale who came in 2nd place and was a killer in the tournament. @chefdavidshim and @jacqhensel held their own on the courts - it was so much fun playing with you guys. Huge thanks to @jinaehong and @tlamanil for repping @cote_nyc and bringing our sizzling Grand Cru Galbi Ssam to the table. Epic day in the books! #wearecityharvest

This was my first time really getting to experience Chicago and what an incredible few days it has been! After many hours walking around town and catching up with new friends and old, I have a newfound love for this beautiful city, its amazing food, hospitality-forward mentality and strong AAPI community. 

On Sunday, we toured around, ate at the famous @portilloshotdogs and attended a number of pre-JBFA events including a truly epic Karaoke gathering. Thank you @perillachicago, @tomoh44, @andrewjlim, @taaforg, @dannyleedc and @miss_hailan for such a fun, celebratory night-to-remember!

Then on Monday morning we were fully revitalized and restored @livebian. Huge thank you to @kevinboehmboka for your incredible hospitality.

Monday evening we finally headed to the James Beard Awards, my first time ever, where everyone looked so incredible. I came with high hopes of witnessing @victoria__james and her team being recognized for their years of hard work. But as I sat through last night’s @beardfoundation awards ceremony, I witnessed something truly memorable.

As an Asian American immigrant, it made me so proud to see a diverse audience of last night’s magnitude - just look at the list of this year’s winners! To watch one person after another walk onto a nationally broadcasted stage and share their struggles and stories of perseverance created such a sense of connection and understanding among all of us in the room. The ‘American Dr.
became a reality for so many people different walks of life last night.

Big changes are not always easy but change is inevitable. This year’s event and list of winners was a giant step with good intentions. Thank you @clarereichenbach, @kristophermoon and the entire Foundation team for all of your work in bringing us all together. I am so grateful to have been in the room to experience and share in such a welcoming, celebratory and inspiring environment.

Dear @cote_nyc,
 
Happy Birthday! I can't believe it's been 6 years since we opened together. Since then, you have served meals to over 600,000 guests, raised millions of dollars for local charitable organizations such as @apexforyouth, @cityharvestnyc, @madsqparknyc, @kacfny and many others, opened up national delivery, @cotewineclub, @undercote, and so much more.

This is far greater than what I could have possibly imagined. This is truly the American Dream and has changed both my life and created a positive impact for so many others. To say I am grateful to you is an understatement.

I am so proud of our team's creativity and commitment to excellence. As we always have been, we will continue to give our 110% and serve the best quality of food, steak, hospitality, and beverage. Thank you so much to our investors, current and former employees, and everyone who has supported us throughout the years: anyone who had a cocktail at the bar, a meal in the restaurant, ordered take-out or delivery or wrote a review with a good intent online. 

Thank you, COTE NYC. You have been an absolute dream and I love you so much for it. 

Happy 6th Birthday!

2/11 World’s Best Steakhouses… IN THE WORLD! 😭 

Words cannot describe how grateful I am for this amazing recognition. More than 15 years ago, I had a dream. I had a dream to open the world’s very first Korean Steakhouse. Then, it was a wild idea: to marry the fun and fire of Korean BBQ with a spirit of regal American Steakhouse with intention of creating something that never existed… the journey was extremely difficult and challenging but along that journey, I met some of the best people in the world. The team grew bigger and stronger. Thanks to their strength and dedication, and His blessings, we stuck to our course and we pushed through…

And today, reading this article from @robbreport truly fills my heart with so much joy, pride, and gratefulness. Thank you to God, family, investors, professional partners, team @cote_nyc , team @cotemiami , Dragon Slayers, and most importantly, our loyal customers who support us day in day out. We will take this great recognition, not just as a job well done, but as an encouragement to continue to put our very best efforts in providing excellent culinary, and hospitality excellence ti our customers. Thanks  @michelinguide for this great honor, and big congratulations to all the amazing steakhouses that’s on this badass list! 

Can’t wait to celebrate it with the team at the best @peterlugersteakhouse

Happy 70th b-day, @jchristopherburch !
Congratulations, @novak.djokovic94 !
Merci, @lebristolparis !

So proud to share the news that we will be opening COTE Singapore in Q4 2023 in @COMOOrchard. This is Gracious Hospitality Management’s first international restaurant ever in one of the most beautiful cities in the world. 
 
I am so humbled to see our business expanding in ways I have always dreamed of - @coqodaq, @550madison, and now @cote_singapore. This new opportunity is something truly special and will hopefully set the bar for Singapore’s already immensely talented dining scene. I seriously can’t wait to open.
 
Every new venture comes after countless sleepless nights, discussion after discussion after discussion. So much pivoting, so much brainstorming, so much perseverance and heart from the entire team. At the end of the day, there’s really one determining factor: My rule of thumb is that I must fall in love with the place and its people. Food is love. So it’s quite simple: I have fallen in love with Singapore and the amazing team that I get to work with there.
 
I am so grateful to Christina Ong for believing in our brand and for her tremendous partnership. COMO Group is one of the most impressive companies I have ever had the honor of working with, and their team is world-class. Thank you Balthazar, Leelyne, Peng Peng, Hui Ying, and everyone else working on this project. Big love to @theofficialpreeti and @mndpc_ny for bringing this vision to life. Thank you so much @chefjgv for the initial intro, for which none of this would have been possible without. Dragon Slayers, here we go. Together, we got this!
 
@chefdavidshim and I are already working on adding some local flavors to make COTE Singapore truly one-of-a-kind. If you’re not based locally, I hope you’ll add it to your travel list. For those in Singapore, I look forward to welcoming you to the COTE family soon!
 
#comoorchard #comoorchardsingapore

One of my favorite restaurant in the world is @wakughin in Singapore. Straight forward, full-contact dining experience at its best form. The best quality ingredients at the hands of a true master chef, Chef Masa. BRAVO! I cannot wait to go back!
To build the best team, you need the best coach. @coqodaq

OUTDOOR DINING ACTION ALERT: 
On behalf of our restaurants and bars, and those across the city of New York, we’re asking all our New York City customers who love dining alfresco to click the link in my bio, which will allow you to quickly send a pre-drafted email to your City Council Member urging them to vote in favor of the Permanent Outdoor Dining law.

In 2020, when the pandemic hit the restaurant industry, we looked to our community & government for support. The Outdoor Dining Act saved not only @cote_nyc, but thousands of our beloved NYC restaurants. On Thursday, 8/3, our City Council Members will be voting on the Permanent Outdoor Dining law which will allow restaurants to keep outdoor seating. While these revenue sources are critical for the survival of our restaurants in this city, this is no longer just a pandemic issue. It is an opportunity to evolve. 
We have a chance to make this beloved city become something even more flavorful and dynamic! It will not be easy and more regulations will have to be made, but this can be a platform to showcase both creativity and ingenuity. Let’s not waste this opportunity! @thenycalliance

Here's what @robbreport had to say: 
"If imitation is the sincerest form of flattery, Simon Kim should be feeling quite flattered these days. Alongside chef David Shim, Kim launched Cote, a restaurant that blends the best of American steakhouses and Korean barbecues in 2017. Since then, numerous imitators have sprung up nationwide. Notably, a restaurant in Texas has emulated Cote to such an extent that even the menu's design looks remarkably similar. However, these copycats have not achieved the same success as Kim. Under the banner of his company, Gracious Hospitality Management, Kim expanded Cote to Miami and Singapore, both awarded Michelin Stars, and is preparing to open a fried chicken restaurant in New York. Kim has also used his influence for good, serving as a board member of City Harvest and founding Taste of Asia, which raised over $1.4 million for charity at its second annual food festival in New York last fall.”

🌟Introducing the COTE Hall of Fame🌟

At COTE, the bonds we’ve formed with our loyal customers have been nothing short of extraordinary. To express our gratitude, and after two years in the making, we’re thrilled to introduce the COTE Hall of Fame: a custom and iconic Butcher’s Block placement exclusively reserved for those who have become integral to the COTE family. 

Immediately upon entering COTE Flatiron, guests can now experience the unique architecture of our new Maru space. Inspired by the traditional Korean Hanok, the Maru serves as a neutral ground, a bridge between “inside” and “outside.” In the spirit of hospitality, our Maru is a place of welcome for anyone. Just like the outer chambers of the traditional Hanok, it beckons neighbors and visitors to come in, rest, and enjoy a moment. Crafted with authenticity, the original Maru wood was shipped directly from Korea and designed by a skilled artisan, preserving the essence of Korean tradition.

Our Maru space was designed by “Moksoo,” a Korean millworker renowned for crafting Korean temples and restoring Hanoks. The result is a space that not only reflects our commitment to tradition but also radiates warmth and hospitality. 

COTE was honored to welcome Kwang-Bok Lee Dopyeonsu 이 광복 도편수 to handcraft the Maru for this project. Dopyeonsu is a highest-ranking designation in Hanok architecture; Lee is a part of the historical lineage of Won-Jae Cho 조 원재's disciple, which dates back to Joseon Dynasty. His works include repair of the Geungnakjeon Hall 긍락전 of Bongjeongsa Temple봉정사 in Korea, the oldest wooden building in Korea and the new construction of the Goryeo Dynasty main hall of Daewonsa Temple 대원사. 

We’re genuinely excited to share the COTE Hall of Fame and the new captivating Maru with you. Join us in celebrating the spirit of gratitude and the unique blend of tradition and modernity this holiday season.

📣 PS: The official rollout of the Hall of Fame program is slated for 2024! We’ll keep you updated through posts and stories on @cotekoreansteakhouse.

We are humbled and honored to have received The Overseas Excellent Korean Restaurant Designation, a highly coveted distinction that is given only to a few select Korean restaurants overseas that best represents our culture, heritage, and excellence.

This distinguished recognition is led by The Korean Food Promotion Institute, with the invaluable support of the Government. The criteria includes alignment with Korean culinary culture, utilization of authentic Korean ingredients, culinary skills, hygiene standards, and 21 other factors meticulously considered in the evaluation process.

We take immense pride in this acknowledgment and are so grateful to our team of dragon slayers, including Executive Chef @chefdavidshim, who uphold our values and dedication to excellence every day. We are committed to continuing our mission to present the power of AND = The best of an American Steakhouse AND the best of Korean BBQ. This recognition holds particular significance as January 13th marked Korean American Day, commemorating the rich heritage and contributions of the Korean-American community to the United States. 🇰🇷🇺🇸
